message: "The reality of what's going on, even in our area, is very unsettling," Mutchler told the audience. "You are not going to sleep well tonight, I guarantee you." Mutchler was part of the three-person panel to talk about human trafficking, a form of modern slavery that experts call the second-largest criminal enterprise in the country, behind only the sale of drugs.

attachments.media_description: Boogeyman targeted: Panel says education key to stopping trafficking
